Last Stand of Elves and Men. Corruption Style by Kevin Werth<br />
        <!--163-->Thin and Stretched x1<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is my first corruption deck. Along with my first deck submited to DeckTech. Any suggestions or problems with my deck, feel free to send your thoughts to gweedo@new.rr.com<br />
                                  -Thanks<br />
<br />
<br />
Sites: Since I&#39;m playing three Aragorn, KiE I really don&#39;t need to play The Prancing Pony. Green Dragon Inn is the my best alternative to site one. Midgewater Marshes hurts Sam and prevents burden removal. Besides, I hate hobbits. Rivendell Valley is a good choice for my fellowship half. Drawing extra cards is always fun. Using Galadriel and site three, you are drawing cards and playing elves for free. Site four adds a burden. I chose Caras Galadhon as my site six. My shadow is not made to swarm, and I have a low companion number.  The Great River is great for a low companion fellowship. It stops Moria swarms. Gates of Argonath is my site eight. Since I only play one maneuver (fellowship) it shouldn&#39;t hurt me any. Fierce minions at site nine are the only way to win with my shadow if the ring-bearer is not corruped.<br />
<br />
Free Peoples: It&#39;s not too difficult to play the fellowship side. It recycles very fast because there are only a few cards with multiple copies. This is needed to make the shadow work. Elrond makes good use by healing Legolas and Aragorn for direct archery. Aragorn, Kie is used to heal Boromir, once I play Horn of Boromir. Using archery allies with the horn makes up for my lack of companions.  There is enough elf healing to go around to use them as fodder every round.<br />
<br />
Shadow: The shadow has two parts. One is corruption. It is not always easy to corrupt the ring-bearer with so many burden removal cards. If corruption is not an answer to winning, over-powering may be key. Using Orc Pillagers, Troopers, and Enduring evil, burdens become more useful. If corruption doesn&#39;t win, just over-kill everyone instead =] </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
